    <!-- Chosen Palette: Forged Steel & Embers -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a narrative sales funnel, guiding the user emotionally from their current pain to the desired solution. The flow is: 1) Hero: A bold, identity-focused headline to hook the user. 2) The Problem: Agitates the user's pain points by contrasting their past self with their present reality. 3) The Solution ("The Community Method"): Introduces the branded solution as a clear, 3-step process, making it feel tangible and unique. 4) Objection Handling: Directly confronts and refutes the primary objection ("no time/energy"). 5) Social Proof: Builds trust using placeholders for video testimonials. 6) The Offer (CTA): A final, urgent call to action to join a waitlist, creating scarcity. This structure is chosen over a simple text layout because it mirrors a proven sales conversation, maximizing persuasive impact and leading the user logically to the conversion point. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: "The Community Method" (3 steps). Goal: Organize & Inform. Viz/Presentation: Interactive 3-column card layout using HTML/CSS. Interaction: Subtle hover effects and scroll-triggered fade-in animations to draw attention to each step. Justification: This visualizes the abstract concept of the program, making it easy to understand and remember. It's more engaging than a bulleted list. Library/Method: Vanilla JS for scroll animations, Tailwind for layout. --- Report Info: Testimonials. Goal: Build Trust. Viz/Presentation: Grid of dark-themed cards with a placeholder for a video thumbnail and a prominent play button icon. Interaction: Hover effects on the play button. Justification: This clearly signals video content, which is more powerful for social proof than text. The visual layout breaks up the page and adds credibility. Library/Method: HTML/Tailwind for cards, CSS for the play icon. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
</head>
